My daughter studied dance for 12 years. Every time I saw her performing ballet, I cried, because she was so graceful and beautiful. Most of the time she was the only person of color on the stage. In all that time, she NEVER had toe shoes that were the color of HER skin. I paid so much money on "flesh tone" shoes that were nowhere near the color of her flesh! Since the shoes were made and molded especially for her foot, I once asked the maker if she could use a fabric that matched my daughter's beautiful chocolate skin. She looked at me like I had committed some sort of blasphemy! So this is especially beautiful and meaningful to me. Thank you.💜
